        <button class="faq-question" onclick="this.parentElement.classList.toggle('open')">
          Can Teamwork Commerce handle admissions, retail, membership, and donations on one device?
          <span class="faq-icon"><i class="ti ti-plus"></i></span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-answer"><p>Yes. The iOS-based Mobile POS handles ticket sales, gift shop merchandise, membership renewals, and donation collection on a single device. Staff can process any transaction type anywhere — in the lobby, gallery, gift shop, or at off-site fundraising events. Donation "round-ups" are built into the core checkout flow, not a plugin.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-question" onclick="this.parentElement.classList.toggle('open')">
          How does Teamwork Commerce compare to KORONA POS, ROLLER, or Blackbaud Altru for museums?
          <span class="faq-icon"><i class="ti ti-plus"></i></span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-answer"><p>KORONA POS offers a solid all-in-one for smaller museums with integrated ticketing, but lacks native RFID, AI clienteling, and global compliance. ROLLER focuses on venue management and capacity but is light on enterprise retail inventory. Blackbaud Altru is strong on donor management but slow at POS and lacks mobile capabilities. Teamwork Commerce is built for larger institutions that need enterprise-grade gift shop inventory (with RFID), unified member LTV tracking across all touchpoints, mobile POS for off-site fundraising, global fiscal compliance (Gift Aid, VAT, GST), and SOC 2 security for government-funded organizations. Shopify and Square keep retail data separate from ticketing entirely.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-question" onclick="this.parentElement.classList.toggle('open')">
          How does Teamwork Commerce compare to Shopify, Square, or Blackbaud Altru for museums?
          <span class="faq-icon"><i class="ti ti-plus"></i></span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-answer"><p>Shopify and Square keep retail data separate from ticketing and membership — they're built for e-commerce and generic retail, not institutional operations. Blackbaud Altru is built for donor management but is often slow at POS and lacks modern mobile capabilities. Teamwork bridges both worlds: a unified visitor profile that tracks every transaction type, real-time gift shop inventory with RFID, 150+ reports, and mobile POS that works at off-site events. One platform for the entire visitor journey.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-question" onclick="this.parentElement.classList.toggle('open')">
          Can we track member lifetime value across gift shop, tickets, and donations?
          <span class="faq-icon"><i class="ti ti-plus"></i></span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-answer"><p>Yes. Teamwork's unified CRM creates a single profile for every visitor that aggregates gift shop purchases, ticket history, membership level, and donation history into one "Value to the Institution" metric. This enables targeted fundraising campaigns, personalized staff interactions, and data-driven membership tier strategies.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-question" onclick="this.parentElement.classList.toggle('open')">
          Does the platform support Gift Aid (UK) and membership-based tax exemptions?
          <span class="faq-icon"><i class="ti ti-plus"></i></span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-answer"><p>Yes. Teamwork Commerce handles Gift Aid for UK institutions and membership-based tax exemptions natively. The platform is localized in 40+ countries with automated fiscal compliance (VAT, GST, NF525, TSE), making it ideal for international museums and cultural institutions.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-question" onclick="this.parentElement.classList.toggle('open')">
          Which museums use Teamwork Commerce?
